http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/%E2%80%98Govt.-schools-will-be-developed-on-the-lines-of-corporate-ones%E2%80%99/article13976337.ece

Minister for Irrigation T. Harish Rao said all necessary facilities would be created in government schools to enable them to compete with corporate ones.Addressing a gathering after distributing furniture worth Rs. 1.4 crore to government schools located at Nanganoor and Chinnakodur mandals on Friday, Mr. Harish Rao said they have already constructed toilets in every household and are supplying drinking water while in the process of achieving some more targets. The furniture was prepared by Bala Vikas, an NGO working for children related issues. “People think that government schools run without proper teachers and furniture. We will change that perspective. Schools now have experienced teachers and we will provide required facilities by and by. The government schools will have digital classrooms and libraries,” said Mr. Harish Rao adding that Siddipet would be soon see schools with all facilities. He instructed the Mandal Educational Officers to visit at least two schools a day and examine the facilities like compound wall, drinking water, plantation of saplings etc. He also distributed cheques worth Rs. 67 lakh to 134 differently-abled couples.Bala Vikas director Shori Reddy said that they have provided infrastructure facilities in about 300 schools in five districts so far. Dustbins and trays were handed over to every classroom during this programme by Bala Vikas.Gurrala Gondi to be developedThe Irrigation Minister promised to develop Gurrala Gondi as a model village. Participating in the golden jubilee celebrations of the Zilla Parishad School in the village on Friday, he said that a school would be established at Gurrala Gondi after the announcement of KG to PG education for all. He also promised to declare Siddipet- Sircilla road as State highway for development of industries.